InclusionRules.name: HbA1c between 7% and 10.5%
InclusionRules.description:
Man or woman with a diagnosis of type 2 diabetes with glycated hemoglobin level 7.0% to
10.5% at screening and be either-
o<U+00A0><U+00A0> (1) not currently on antihyperglycemic agent (AHA) therapy or<U+00A0>
o<U+00A0><U+00A0> (2) on AHA monotherapy or combination therapy with any approved class of
agents: e.g., sulfonylurea, metformin, peroxisome proliferator-activated receptor gamma
(PPAR) agonist, alpha-glucosidase inhibitor, glucagon-like peptide-1 (GLP-1) analogue,
dipeptidyl peptidase-4 (DPP-4) inhibitor, or insulin.

InclusionRules.name: Postmenopausal
InclusionRules.description:
Women must be:
<U+2013> Postmenopausal, defined as >45 years of age with amenorrhea for at least 18 months, or >45 years of age with amenorrhea for at least 6 months and less than 18 months and a serum follicle stimulating hormone (FSH) level >40 IU/ml, 
<U+2013> or Surgically sterile (have had a hysterectomy or bilateral oophorectomy, tubal ligation), or otherwise be incapable of pregnancy, 
<U+2013> or Heterosexually active and practicing a highly effective method of birth control, including hormonal prescription oral contraceptives, contraceptive injections, contraceptive patch, intrauterine device, double-barrier method (e.g., condoms, diaphragm, or cervical cap with spermicidal foam, cream, or gel), or male partner sterilization, consistent with local regulations regarding use of birth control methods for subjects participating in clinical trials, for the dur<U+2013> or Not heterosexually active.
Note: subjects who are not heterosexually active at screening must agree to utilize a highly effective method of birth control if they become heterosexually active during their
participation in the study.ation of their participation in the study,

InclusionRules.name: Other inclusion criteria #1
InclusionRules.description:
Women of childbearing potential must have a negative urine -human chorionic
gonadotropin (-hCG) pregnancy test at screening and baseline (predose, Day 1).

InclusionRules.name: No history of diabetic ketoacidosis
InclusionRules.description: History of diabetic ketoacidosis, type 1 diabetes, pancreas or beta-cell transplantation, or diabetes secondary to pancreatitis or pancreatectomy.

InclusionRules.name: On an AHA and not on a stable regimen (i.e., agents and doses) for at least 8 weeks before the screening visit and through the screening/run-in period.
InclusionRules.description: Note: a stable dose of insulin is defined as no change in the insulin regimen (i.e., type[s] of insulin) and 15% change in the total daily dose of insulin (averaged over 1 week to account for day-to-day variability).

InclusionRules.name: For patients on a sulfonylurea agent or on insulin: fasting fingerstick glucose at site <110 mg/dl (<6 mmol/l) at Baseline/Day 1.
InclusionRules.description:
Note: at the investigator’s discretion, based upon an assessment of recent self-monitored
blood glucose (SMBG) values, subjects meeting either of these fingerstick glucose exclusion
criteria may continue the single-blind placebo and return to the investigational site within
14 days and may be randomized if the repeat fasting fingerstick value no longer meets the
exclusion criterion. Subjects with fingerstick glucose >270 mg/dl (>15 mmol/l) may have
their AHA regimen adjusted and be rescreened once on a stable regimen for at least 8 weeks.

InclusionRules.name: No history of hypoglycemic episode
InclusionRules.description:
History of one or more severe hypoglycemic episode within 6 months before screening.
Note: a severe hypoglycemic episode is defined as an event that requires the help of
another person.

InclusionRules.name: No history of hereditary glucose-galactose malabsoprtion or primary renal glucosuria
Ongoing, inadequately controlled thyroid disorder. Note: subjects on thyroid hormone-replacement therapy must be on a stable dose for at least 6 weeks before Day 1.
No renal disease
InclusionRules.description:
Renal disease that required treatment with immunosuppressive therapy or a history of
dialysis or renal transplant.
Note: subjects with a history of treated childhood renal disease, without sequelae, may
participate.

InclusionRules.name: No CV within 3 months
InclusionRules.description:
MI, unstable angina, revascularization procedure, or cerebrovascular accident within 3
months before screening, or a planned revascularization procedure, or history of New York
Heart Association (NYHA) Class IV cardiac disease.

InclusionRules.name: No eGFR<30
InclusionRules.description:
Estimated glomerular filtration rate (eGFR) <30 ml/min/1.73 m2 at screening (provided by
the central laboratory)
<U+2013> For subjects taking metformin: at screening, serum creatinine 1.4 mg/dl (124 mol/l) for
men or 1.3 mg/dl (115 mol/l) for women; no contraindication to the use of metformin
(including eGFR) based on the label of the country of investigational site

InclusionRules.name: No liver lab abnormality
InclusionRules.description:
ALT levels >2.0 times the upper limit of normal (ULN) 
or total bilirubin >1.5 times the ULN at screening, 
unless in the opinion of the investigator and as agreed upon by the sponsor’s medical officer, the findings are consistent with Gilbert’s disease.

InclusionRules.name: No hematological disorder
InclusionRules.description:
Subject has a current clinically important hematological disorder (e.g., symptomatic
anemia, proliferative bone marrow disorder, thrombocytopenia).
- ICD-9 Diagnosis Codes: 238.4x, 289.83, 238.71, 280.x-285.x, 287.3x, 287.4x, 287.5x

InclusionRules.name: No major surgery
InclusionRules.description:
Major surgery (i.e., requiring general anesthesia) within 3 months of the screening visit or
any surgery planned during the subject’s expected participation in the study (except minor
surgery; i.e., outpatient surgery under local anesthesia).

InclusionRules.name: No current use of SGLT2 inhibitor
Other exclusion criteria #4
InclusionRules.description: Known allergies, hypersensitivity, or intolerance to canagliflozin or its excipients.

InclusionRules.name: No Current use of a corticosteroid or immunosuppressive agent
InclusionRules.description:
Current use of a corticosteroid medication or immunosuppressive agent, or likely to require
treatment with a corticosteroid medication (for longer than 2 weeks in duration) or an
immunosuppressive agent. Note: subjects using inhaled, intranasal, intra-articular, or
topical corticosteroids, or corticosteroids in therapeutic replacement doses may
participate.

InclusionRules.name: Other exclusion criteria #5
InclusionRules.description:
Received an active investigational drug (including vaccines) or used an investigational
medical device within 3 months before Day 1/baseline or received at least one dose of
canagliflozin in a prior study.

InclusionRules.name: No drug or alcohol abuse (3 yrs)
